A lawsuit alleges Johns Hopkins University and the Rockefeller Foundation helped conduct a similar study in Guatemala from 1945 to 1956 . 
  Orphans, inmates and prostitutes were deliberately infected with sexually transmitted diseases . 
  The subjects of the experiments weren't told they were infected . 
  The suit seeks more than $1 billion in damages . 
  Johns Hopkins and Rockefeller Foundation deny responsibility for the experiments . 
 